[1]+ sleep 5000 &
renuka@Bunny:~$ jobs
[1]+  Running                 sleep 5000 &
renuka@Bunny:~$ kill 1
-bash: kill: (1) - Operation not permitted
renuka@Bunny:~$ pkill sleep
[1]+  Terminated              sleep 5000
--------------------------------------------------
Foreground: You see it on screen and must wait for it to finish.
fg	Bring job to foreground	fg	Terminal waits for it to finish
fg %2	Bring specific job	fg %2	Job 2 moves to foreground
renuka@Bunny:~$ sleep 100
^Z
[1]+  Stopped                 sleep 100
renuka@Bunny:~$ bg
[1]+ sleep 100 &
renuka@Bunny:~$ jobs
[1]+  Running                 sleep 100 &
renuka@Bunny:~$ fg
sleep 100
Background: It runs silently behind the scenes â€” you can still use your terminal.
